1
00:00:01,468 --> 00:00:04,171
Gon: I just never thought

2
00:00:04,204 --> 00:00:08,709
that being weak and powerless
could be so frustrating!

3
00:00:08,742 --> 00:00:10,978
♪

4
00:00:13,146 --> 00:00:14,748
Killua: Gon...

5
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:19,954
for the 30 days
that you can’t use nen...

6
00:00:19,987 --> 00:00:22,623
I’ll protect you.

7
00:00:22,656 --> 00:00:26,960
Whatever it takes,
i’ll keep you safe.

8
00:00:26,994 --> 00:00:27,962
♪

9
00:00:27,995 --> 00:00:29,997
( Singing in Japanese )

10
00:01:11,438 --> 00:01:13,440
♪

11
00:01:19,379 --> 00:01:20,680
Narrator: Colt arrived

12
00:01:20,714 --> 00:01:22,749
carrying a white flag
of surrender

13
00:01:22,783 --> 00:01:25,352
to ask the hunters
for a favor.

14
00:01:25,385 --> 00:01:29,422
His desperate wish was that
they save the dying queen.

15
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:31,525
After hearing his request,

16
00:01:31,558 --> 00:01:35,429
morel and knov
took Colt to see netero.

17
00:01:35,462 --> 00:01:38,532
Netero: It’s me.
I want you to send over

18
00:01:38,565 --> 00:01:41,635
the chimera ant
research team immediately.

19
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:46,440
Yes. The king has been born.

20
00:01:46,473 --> 00:01:50,243
contact Dr. Lee
of the fanlin medical college.

21
00:01:50,277 --> 00:01:52,613
have her assemble
a team of the best surgeons

22
00:01:52,646 --> 00:01:56,483
and artificial organ engineering
specialists she can find.

23
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:00,454
- hmm.
- ( Hangs up )

24
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:03,457
Be ready to leave here
in four hours.

25
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:05,225
- Morel: Yes, sir.
- Knov: Yes, sir.

26
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:11,364
( Both gasp )

27
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,837
Netero: We will do absolutely
everything in our power.

28
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:20,273
And, Colt...

29
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:24,678
We’re going to need your help
to accomplish this.

30
00:02:24,711 --> 00:02:25,779
( Colt grunts )

31
00:02:30,517 --> 00:02:33,120
( Netero sighs )

32
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:36,490
this might just be
the last time I wear this.

33
00:02:36,523 --> 00:02:38,458
Morel: Hey, so is that...

34
00:02:38,492 --> 00:02:41,695
knov: It is,
his "heart" t-shirt.

35
00:02:41,728 --> 00:02:44,297
They say it’s a lucky outfit

36
00:02:44,331 --> 00:02:47,367
that he only wears
when he fights for real.

37
00:02:47,401 --> 00:02:49,703
( Netero breathing deeply )

38
00:02:49,736 --> 00:02:52,205
Knov: I thought
it was just a rumor.

39
00:02:52,239 --> 00:02:55,509
netero: Now then, Colt,
it appears that you can use nen.

40
00:03:02,182 --> 00:03:04,151
Since you’ve been
in the presence

41
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:06,420
of the new king once before,

42
00:03:06,453 --> 00:03:10,123
your opinion on this matter
would be rather helpful,

43
00:03:10,157 --> 00:03:14,828
so be honest.
How do I compare to the king?

44
00:03:14,862 --> 00:03:17,498
Morel: It really is amazing.

45
00:03:17,531 --> 00:03:21,835
It feels like little needles
stabbing all over my body.

46
00:03:23,871 --> 00:03:26,273
Colt: I doubt...

47
00:03:26,306 --> 00:03:28,441
That you’ll be able
to lay a finger on him.

48
00:03:28,475 --> 00:03:29,843
- Morel: Huh?
- Knov: Hmm?

49
00:03:29,877 --> 00:03:32,747
Colt: You’ll be killed
by one of his royal guards

50
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:34,581
before you can even get close.

51
00:03:35,849 --> 00:03:37,918
( Netero laughs )

52
00:03:37,951 --> 00:03:39,653
I see.

53
00:03:39,686 --> 00:03:41,855
That’s good to hear.

54
00:03:41,889 --> 00:03:45,860
I’ve found a challenger
at my age.

55
00:03:45,893 --> 00:03:48,462
This is thrilling,
quite thrilling.

56
00:03:49,496 --> 00:03:51,865
( Both gasp )

57
00:03:51,899 --> 00:03:56,670
Netero: Now, morel, the pupils
will be decided today, correct?

58
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:58,939
- morel: Right.
- Netero: Go with Colt,

59
00:03:58,972 --> 00:04:01,675
and gather the Victors
and research team together.

60
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:04,277
Then quickly get everyone
over to the nest.

61
00:04:04,311 --> 00:04:05,579
Morel: And you, sir?

62
00:04:05,612 --> 00:04:07,681
You can’t pursue the king alone.

63
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:08,882
Netero: Oh, no.

64
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:12,653
i’m off to see
an old friend of mine.

65
00:04:14,721 --> 00:04:17,290
♪

66
00:04:28,335 --> 00:04:30,671
Morel: Don’t forget
my million, okay?

67
00:04:30,704 --> 00:04:32,673
Knov: Oh, you’ll get your money.

68
00:04:32,706 --> 00:04:35,242
Knuckle: What are
you guys talking about?

69
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:36,777
Morel: Nothing important.

70
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:37,878
Colt: Let’s go.

71
00:04:37,911 --> 00:04:38,945
Morel: All right.

72
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:44,918
Bihorn: Everyone else
has already left.

73
00:04:44,952 --> 00:04:47,855
Panda ant: Sure looks that way.
Most of our soldiers

74
00:04:47,888 --> 00:04:50,491
went off and joined
one of the other squads,

75
00:04:50,524 --> 00:04:53,894
except for a handful
of oddballs that defected.

76
00:04:53,927 --> 00:04:55,929
They all decided to stay here.

77
00:04:55,963 --> 00:04:58,265
Colt: We’re fortunate.

78
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,967
I would have expected
some fighting to break out.

79
00:05:01,001 --> 00:05:03,537
( Instruments clattering )

80
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:04,771
Doctor: Update me.

81
00:05:04,805 --> 00:05:06,740
were you the one
who stopped the bleeding?

82
00:05:06,773 --> 00:05:08,341
Octopus ant: Yes, but i’m afraid

83
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,744
there wasn’t anything else
I could do for her.

84
00:05:10,777 --> 00:05:12,912
Doctor: I’m not sure
we can either.

85
00:05:12,946 --> 00:05:14,948
Don’t expect a miracle.

86
00:05:14,982 --> 00:05:16,584
For the moment,

87
00:05:16,617 --> 00:05:19,353
we’ll attach as many
artificial organs as we can.

88
00:05:19,386 --> 00:05:21,688
Colt: Can you use my organs?

89
00:05:21,722 --> 00:05:23,958
you can have
all of my blood as well.

90
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:25,559
( Morel gasps )

91
00:05:25,592 --> 00:05:27,594
Doctor: I’m sorry,
but that won’t work.

92
00:05:27,628 --> 00:05:30,030
chimera ants
from different generations

93
00:05:30,063 --> 00:05:31,965
are completely
different organisms.

94
00:05:31,999 --> 00:05:34,835
Just look around you.
You’ll see how much

95
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:37,971
the chimera ants
in your own generation vary.

96
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:39,473
( Colt gasps )

97
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:41,575
Doctor: Thank you, nonetheless.

98
00:05:41,608 --> 00:05:43,877
We promise to do our best.

99
00:05:46,613 --> 00:05:51,017
Let’s just pray that all
these organs keep her alive.

100
00:05:52,019 --> 00:05:53,988
( Monitor beeping )

101
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,423
♪

102
00:06:15,042 --> 00:06:16,677
( Colt groans )

103
00:06:17,845 --> 00:06:19,980
Pray?

104
00:06:20,013 --> 00:06:23,950
damn it.
Is that really all I can do?

105
00:06:25,085 --> 00:06:27,421
- Queen: Someone...
- ( Colt gasps )

106
00:06:28,488 --> 00:06:31,424
Queen: Is anyone there?

107
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:34,561
colt: Yes!
I’m right by your side.

108
00:06:34,595 --> 00:06:36,530
Is there anything you need?

109
00:06:36,563 --> 00:06:37,931
Morel: What is it?

110
00:06:37,965 --> 00:06:39,934
- Doctor: A signal?
- Octopus ant: Correct.

111
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:41,936
the queen is
not capable of speech

112
00:06:41,969 --> 00:06:43,671
like the rest of us are.

113
00:06:43,704 --> 00:06:45,439
Doctor: Can you
interpret for me?

114
00:06:45,472 --> 00:06:48,942
She may give us a hint
as to how to save her life.

115
00:06:48,976 --> 00:06:50,945
♪

116
00:06:50,978 --> 00:06:52,847
Queen: Tell me.

117
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:55,850
My son, how is he?

118
00:06:55,883 --> 00:06:57,551
Is he all right?

119
00:06:58,785 --> 00:07:01,921
Was there anything...
Wrong with him?

120
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:03,557
Anything at all?

121
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,559
Octopus ant: "Anything at all?"

122
00:07:06,994 --> 00:07:09,530
( Colt gasps )

123
00:07:09,563 --> 00:07:10,864
Don’t worry.

124
00:07:10,898 --> 00:07:14,969
He is perfectly healthy,
and right now--

125
00:07:15,002 --> 00:07:16,737
right now
he’s taken the royal guard

126
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,573
to look for herbs, anything
that might help heal you.

127
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:22,576
octopus ant:
"...That might help heal you."

128
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:23,977
( Sighs )

129
00:07:24,011 --> 00:07:26,080
the truth is
that after he killed

130
00:07:26,113 --> 00:07:28,449
and ate
some of the squad leaders,

131
00:07:28,482 --> 00:07:30,584
he left to find
a new territory.

132
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:32,886
I doubt he will ever return.

133
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,388
Knuckle: Ate them?!

134
00:07:34,421 --> 00:07:35,389
Octopus ant: Yes.

135
00:07:35,422 --> 00:07:37,457
It seems that the king

136
00:07:37,491 --> 00:07:40,561
has no concern for
the queen’s health whatsoever.

137
00:07:40,594 --> 00:07:41,595
Knuckle: Eh?

138
00:07:41,628 --> 00:07:44,464
Queen: Then he’s safe?

139
00:07:44,498 --> 00:07:46,567
The king is safe?

140
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,801
Colt: Yes.

141
00:07:47,835 --> 00:07:49,737
( Queen sighs )

142
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:52,573
I’m so glad.

143
00:07:52,606 --> 00:07:55,008
( Gasps ) No.

144
00:07:55,042 --> 00:07:59,914
You must send the king
on his journey right away.

145
00:07:59,947 --> 00:08:01,215
( Colt gasps )

146
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:05,920
Queen: He does not have time
to concern himself

147
00:08:05,953 --> 00:08:09,824
with trifling matters, like me.

148
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:17,564
He has within him the potential
to rule the entire world.

149
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:22,102
I was so worried,

150
00:08:22,135 --> 00:08:26,473
because he was born prematurely.

151
00:08:26,507 --> 00:08:29,176
However, it appears...

152
00:08:29,209 --> 00:08:33,880
That I have finally
fulfilled my destiny.

153
00:08:33,914 --> 00:08:35,916
♪

154
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:42,823
That’s enough for me.

155
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:44,624
Colt: What are you saying?!

156
00:08:44,658 --> 00:08:47,628
You are our guiding force,
my queen.

157
00:08:47,661 --> 00:08:52,833
Without you, the rest of us will
surely lose our way and perish.

158
00:08:55,169 --> 00:08:58,973
Queen: I know my body
better than anyone else,

159
00:08:59,006 --> 00:09:03,244
and I can say with certainty

160
00:09:03,277 --> 00:09:07,648
I do not have long to live.

161
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:15,489
Even so, I have no regrets,

162
00:09:15,522 --> 00:09:17,057
not one.

163
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:18,658
Colt: Please stop!

164
00:09:20,093 --> 00:09:22,662
My queen, you have to live!

165
00:09:22,696 --> 00:09:25,699
Use my body! It’s the only way!

166
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:28,268
come on!
You have to try, at least!

167
00:09:30,037 --> 00:09:31,872
Doctor: Listen to her.

168
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:33,507
Respect her wishes.

169
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,075
They may be her last.

170
00:09:35,108 --> 00:09:37,611
( Colt gasps )

171
00:09:37,644 --> 00:09:43,583
Queen: I have one final request.

172
00:09:45,953 --> 00:09:49,890
I-I thought of a name...

173
00:09:49,923 --> 00:09:54,127
For him, for the king.

174
00:09:55,329 --> 00:09:57,898
Colt: A name?

175
00:09:59,266 --> 00:10:02,102
Queen: Meruem.

176
00:10:03,637 --> 00:10:09,076
It means the light
that illuminates all.

177
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:11,311
( Gasps )

178
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:14,581
Let...

179
00:10:15,649 --> 00:10:17,718
Him know...

180
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:20,320
( Colt crying )

181
00:10:21,755 --> 00:10:23,257
Queen: My...

182
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:26,960
Beloved son.

183
00:10:26,994 --> 00:10:29,330
( Gasps )

184
00:10:30,931 --> 00:10:32,966
( Flatline tone whines )

185
00:10:41,008 --> 00:10:43,878
♪

186
00:10:45,379 --> 00:10:46,914
( Colt gasps )

187
00:10:46,947 --> 00:10:51,018
I failed to protect her again.

188
00:10:54,388 --> 00:10:56,357
I’m useless.

189
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:59,360
I can’t protect anyone.

190
00:10:59,393 --> 00:11:01,161
( Doctor sighs )

191
00:11:01,195 --> 00:11:03,097
( Knuckle stifling sobs )

192
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:04,765
Knov: "Again," huh?

193
00:11:04,798 --> 00:11:07,134
Has this happened before?

194
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:09,269
panda ant:
No, he’s probably referring

195
00:11:09,303 --> 00:11:11,372
to a memory
from when he was human.

196
00:11:11,405 --> 00:11:12,973
- ( Men gasp )
- Morel: Memories?

197
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,875
You have human memories?

198
00:11:14,908 --> 00:11:17,110
panda ant:
Yeah, of course we do,

199
00:11:17,144 --> 00:11:19,780
though some of us remember
better than others.

200
00:11:19,813 --> 00:11:22,215
Our previous human personalities

201
00:11:22,249 --> 00:11:24,985
strongly influence
our behavior now,

202
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:26,786
but there are many of us

203
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:29,389
that can still remember
our human names.

204
00:11:29,423 --> 00:11:33,127
if you’ve ever wondered
how we learned to talk so fast,

205
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,361
that’s how.

206
00:11:34,394 --> 00:11:35,395
( Morel sighs )

207
00:11:49,343 --> 00:11:50,811
Colt: Eh?

208
00:11:50,844 --> 00:11:52,212
Huh?

209
00:11:52,246 --> 00:11:53,814
Octopus ant: Hmm?

210
00:11:53,847 --> 00:11:56,216
Colt: What’s that?

211
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:57,418
( Men gasp )

212
00:11:57,451 --> 00:12:00,187
( Chimera ants gasp )

213
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,822
Octopus ant: Look!

214
00:12:01,855 --> 00:12:04,291
There’s something moving!

215
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:07,728
Colt: Don’t!

216
00:12:08,862 --> 00:12:13,033
Stand back. I’ll get it myself.

217
00:12:17,871 --> 00:12:20,040
( Octopus ant gasps )

218
00:12:41,161 --> 00:12:43,463
( Chimera ant crying )

219
00:13:03,517 --> 00:13:05,486
Colt: I will protect...

220
00:13:05,519 --> 00:13:07,755
This baby.

221
00:13:08,856 --> 00:13:10,758
I swear it.

222
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:14,495
I won’t fail, not this time.

223
00:13:14,528 --> 00:13:15,996
( Knuckle stifling sobs )

224
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:17,397
( Morel clicks tongue )

225
00:13:17,431 --> 00:13:20,200
♪

226
00:13:29,843 --> 00:13:31,011
Knov: Morel?

227
00:13:32,045 --> 00:13:35,815
Morel: Colt, can you promise me

228
00:13:35,849 --> 00:13:39,019
that neither of you
will ever eat a human?

229
00:13:43,857 --> 00:13:47,427
If you can’t make that promise,

230
00:13:47,461 --> 00:13:51,432
then you should get
out of my sight immediately.

231
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:56,236
But if you’re willing
to give me your word...

232
00:14:00,174 --> 00:14:03,144
I won’t let anyone harm you two,

233
00:14:03,177 --> 00:14:05,813
not as long
as i’m around, anyway.

234
00:14:05,846 --> 00:14:08,849
No enemy gets past me...

235
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:12,019
And that is a promise.

236
00:14:12,052 --> 00:14:13,253
( Snorts )

237
00:14:13,287 --> 00:14:15,289
♪

238
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:18,559
( Knuckle laughs )

239
00:14:18,592 --> 00:14:21,061
There’s no doubt about it.

240
00:14:21,094 --> 00:14:23,863
My master has a soft side.

241
00:14:23,897 --> 00:14:26,533
That must be where I got mine!

242
00:14:26,567 --> 00:14:29,103
( Chimera ant crying )

243
00:15:01,335 --> 00:15:03,337
( Gon crying )

244
00:15:20,554 --> 00:15:23,123
( Screams )

245
00:15:25,359 --> 00:15:27,628
Gon: Right! I’m over it now.

246
00:15:27,661 --> 00:15:30,430
Knuckle and the other hunters
are gonna save kite.

247
00:15:30,464 --> 00:15:31,899
I’m sure of it,

248
00:15:31,932 --> 00:15:35,035
so I have to get
a whole lot stronger,

249
00:15:35,068 --> 00:15:39,239
because kite’s coming back,
and I won’t disappoint him.

250
00:15:40,674 --> 00:15:43,443
Spin: So your head’s
on straight after all.

251
00:15:44,678 --> 00:15:47,247
It’s true that you
may have met kite

252
00:15:47,281 --> 00:15:49,283
before we did,
but the fact remains

253
00:15:49,316 --> 00:15:52,586
that we’ve spent much more time
with him than you have.

254
00:15:54,188 --> 00:15:55,890
If you were still moping around

255
00:15:55,923 --> 00:15:57,158
after we’d
crossed the mountains,

256
00:15:57,191 --> 00:15:58,659
I was gonna beat you up.

257
00:15:58,692 --> 00:16:00,294
( Gon gasps )

258
00:16:00,327 --> 00:16:02,029
Spin: Then i’d tell you

259
00:16:02,062 --> 00:16:05,265
kite wouldn’t want to see
you two like this.

260
00:16:05,299 --> 00:16:07,334
i’m positive
that he’s still alive,

261
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:09,002
and i’m absolutely certain

262
00:16:09,036 --> 00:16:11,272
he wouldn’t want the two of you
to have any regrets.

263
00:16:11,305 --> 00:16:14,675
The question is what to do now.

264
00:16:14,708 --> 00:16:16,643
You should choose wisely

265
00:16:16,677 --> 00:16:19,480
and find the will
to follow through.

266
00:16:19,513 --> 00:16:22,182
If you’re too weak,
then just train more.

267
00:16:22,216 --> 00:16:23,451
There’s enough space in here

268
00:16:23,483 --> 00:16:25,485
for you two
to do some squats and push-ups.

269
00:16:25,519 --> 00:16:29,089
Gon: Yeah. You’re right!

270
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:34,495
Hey, spin...

271
00:16:34,528 --> 00:16:35,696
Spin: Hmm?

272
00:16:35,729 --> 00:16:39,299
Gon: Why do you
want to be a hunter?

273
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:42,002
Spin: Because I need the money

274
00:16:42,035 --> 00:16:44,604
so that I can repay
an enormous debt.

275
00:16:47,241 --> 00:16:49,577
have you heard
of the small-billed swan?

276
00:16:49,610 --> 00:16:50,611
Gon: No.

277
00:16:50,644 --> 00:16:52,679
Spin: It’s a species of bird

278
00:16:52,713 --> 00:16:55,149
that only live
around a certain mine.

279
00:16:55,182 --> 00:16:59,153
No one’s been able to figure out
exactly why that is yet.

280
00:16:59,186 --> 00:17:01,155
The food, the water,
the weather,

281
00:17:01,188 --> 00:17:02,623
nothing really explains it.

282
00:17:02,656 --> 00:17:04,358
♪

283
00:17:04,391 --> 00:17:08,395
So we bought the entire area
where the mine is located.

284
00:17:09,463 --> 00:17:11,632
Or rather...

285
00:17:11,665 --> 00:17:14,067
Where what’s left of it is.

286
00:17:16,069 --> 00:17:17,637
Kite financed it for us.

287
00:17:17,671 --> 00:17:21,008
We were just kids who had
nothing to offer in return,

288
00:17:21,041 --> 00:17:23,043
and when we couldn’t find
a single adult

289
00:17:23,076 --> 00:17:25,779
who’d listen to us, he did.

290
00:17:29,082 --> 00:17:32,252
stick and I
both come from that area.

291
00:17:32,286 --> 00:17:34,088
We were born there.

292
00:17:40,494 --> 00:17:42,262
( Swans warbling )

293
00:17:43,597 --> 00:17:46,166
I remember the sight

294
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,569
of thousands
of small-billed swans

295
00:17:48,602 --> 00:17:53,273
taking flight with the light
of dawn at their backs.

296
00:17:53,307 --> 00:17:57,344
it’s the most vivid and
lasting memory stick and I have.

297
00:18:00,714 --> 00:18:02,516
When we found out the area

298
00:18:02,549 --> 00:18:05,252
was slated to become
an industrial waste site,

299
00:18:05,285 --> 00:18:10,257
we finally realized how
important all of it was to us.

300
00:18:10,290 --> 00:18:14,294
Kite told me once
he envied the two of us.

301
00:18:14,328 --> 00:18:17,264
He doesn’t have
a place to call home,

302
00:18:17,297 --> 00:18:20,300
because he doesn’t know
where he was born.

303
00:18:23,136 --> 00:18:26,139
once this mission
is finally over and done with,

304
00:18:26,173 --> 00:18:28,709
i’d really like
to take the two of you there...

305
00:18:31,078 --> 00:18:32,846
To my treasure.

306
00:18:42,756 --> 00:18:44,758
( Footsteps )

307
00:18:50,164 --> 00:18:51,732
( Knuckle and shoot grunt )

308
00:18:52,766 --> 00:18:55,535
( Scraping, fluttering echoing )

309
00:18:55,569 --> 00:18:57,571
♪

310
00:19:21,461 --> 00:19:22,762
Knuckle: Huh?!

311
00:19:22,796 --> 00:19:25,232
Damn. This is...

312
00:19:25,265 --> 00:19:27,267
( Scraping, fluttering )

313
00:19:30,337 --> 00:19:32,339
♪

314
00:19:38,278 --> 00:19:39,646
( Woman gasps )

315
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:42,650
( Groans )

316
00:19:46,887 --> 00:19:48,722
Cheetu: Finish line!

317
00:19:51,692 --> 00:19:54,862
I truly am the king of speed.

318
00:19:54,895 --> 00:19:55,863
( Slurps )

319
00:19:55,896 --> 00:19:59,266
No one can stop me.

320
00:19:59,299 --> 00:20:01,268
Whoo-hoo!

321
00:20:04,271 --> 00:20:05,839
Alligator ant:
Given cheetu’s speed,

322
00:20:05,873 --> 00:20:09,477
it’s a good bet that he’s
already crossed the border.

323
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:13,447
Well, I guess I can
take my time searching.

324
00:20:14,615 --> 00:20:17,485
But i’ll find my own paradise

325
00:20:17,518 --> 00:20:20,588
with plenty of food and females.

326
00:20:20,621 --> 00:20:25,659
Cows, pigs, humans,
boars, bears,

327
00:20:25,692 --> 00:20:28,728
i don’t even care,
as long as they’re plentiful.

328
00:20:29,963 --> 00:20:32,199
Because i’m the king,

329
00:20:32,232 --> 00:20:33,800
the king of eaters.

330
00:20:37,571 --> 00:20:40,574
Narrator: The chimera ants
that were once soldiers

331
00:20:40,607 --> 00:20:45,412
have now departed in order
to become kings themselves.

332
00:20:59,459 --> 00:21:01,628
Meanwhile the king himself

333
00:21:01,662 --> 00:21:04,899
is now in the Republic
of east gorteau.

334
00:21:14,942 --> 00:21:16,510
King: Hmm.

335
00:21:25,719 --> 00:21:26,687
♪

336
00:21:26,954 --> 00:21:28,956
( Singing in Japanese )

